<ol>
  <li>
    <p>Colonel Fitzwilliam seemed really glad to see them. Anything was a welcome relief to him at Rosings, and Mrs. Collins’s pretty friend had, moreover, <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="caught his fancy very much"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(非常讨他的欢心)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>And they conversed <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="with so much spirit and flow"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(非常起劲、滔滔不绝)</code></b>, as to draw the attention of Lady Catherine herself, as well as of Mr. Darcy.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>I shall not say that you are mistaken, because you could not really believe me to <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="entertain any design of alarming you"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(心存任何要吓唬你的企图)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>They have not the same force or rapidity, and do not produce the same <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="expression"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(情感表现)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>If I had ever learnt, I should have been a great proficient. And so would Anne, if her health had allowed her to <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="apply (联系之前的那句 Vanity had given her application. - 虚荣让她勤奋好学。)"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(努力工作/全神贯注工作)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p><b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="So much the better"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(这样更好)</code></b>. It cannot be done too much. And when I next write to her, I shall <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="charge"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(嘱咐)</code></b> her not to neglect it <b data-toggle="tooltip" data-original-title="not on any account = on no account 绝不"><code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">________(绝不)</code></b>.</p>
  </li>
  <li>
    <p>I am particularly unlucky in meeting with a person so well able to expose my real character, in a part of the world where I had hoped to 
